  "body": "Many plotting functions have a \"legacy\" version, designated either in the name or the docstring. We could officially deprecate them, and then remove them.\r\n\r\nI believe the \"legacy\" refers to accepting `shap_values` numpy arrays directly, rather than the newer-style `Explanation` objects.\r\n\r\n## Legacy things to remove:\r\n\r\nLegacy plotting functions:\r\n\r\n- [ ] `bar_legacy`\r\n- [ ] `summary_legacy`\r\n- [ ] `dependence_legacy`\r\n- [ ] `waterfall_legacy`\r\n\r\n\r\nSuspected unused / dead code:\r\n\r\n- [ ] `shap/utils/_masked_models.py:_build_delta_masked_inputs()`\r\n- [ ] `shap/plots/_text.py:text_old()`\r\n- [ ] `shap/explainers/_explainer.py:Explainer._compute_main_effects()`\r\n\r\nPossibly related other legacy things:\r\n\r\n- [ ] The module `shap.utils._legacy.py`\r\n- [ ] The method `Permutation.shap_values`\r\n- [ ] `Partition.owen()` vs `Partition.owen3()` (?)\r\n",
